    "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India",
    "title": "India",
    "content": "India is a federal union comprising 28 states and 8 union territories. It is characterized by immense linguistic, cultural, and geographical diversity. Its history spans five millennia, marked by the rise and fall of various empires and significant contributions to world civilization, including the Indus Valley Civilization. Modern India emerged from British colonial rule in 1947, establishing itself as a secular, socialist republic. The economy is one of the fastest-growing major economies globally, driven by services, industry, and agriculture, though it continues to grapple with significant developmental challenges and inequality.",
    "snippet": "India, officially the Republic of India, is a country in South Asia. It is the seventh-largest country by area, the second-most populous country, and the most populous democracy in the world. India shares land borders with Pakistan to the west; China, Nepal, and Bhutan to the north; and Bangladesh and Myanmar to the east.",
    "created_at": "2026-01-19T19:35:58.110994Z",
